nts1.n: CARLOS RENÉ: CUMBIA EN MARACAY - VENEZUELAN CUMBIA & PORRO (R)
nts1.d: Spanning the late 1950s to the late 1970s, this selection highlights Venezuela’s take on big band cumbia. With strong ties to Colombian cumbia, especially in cities like Maracaibo and Caracas, local orchestras blended its rhythms with their own style. Some tracks reinterpret Colombian classics with a distinct Venezuelan touch, while many are original compositions that showcase the country’s unique approach to the genre.

Made for peaceful places at high volume.
Hopefully this mix is as soothing for the listener as it is for myself. It's a mix of various tracks from all over the place and I hope it is enjoyed.

nts2.n: Sea Of Tranquility w/ Charlie Villas
nts2.d:
Sea of Tranquility is for the nights alone with your thoughts… for the ride home…for the moment the world feels too loud and you need to slip beneath the surface and take a deep breath…
I’m usually playing for dancefloors. Bodies are moving, energy is peaking and so this felt like a welcome change. A chance to slow down. To listen inward. To lean into the songs that steady me… the ones I reach for when I’m going through it. These are the tracks that restore my nervous system. May it do the same for you.

nts2.n: watch my mum dance w/ bbymix
nts2.d:
Peace for me feels like spring: hilltop at sunrise, bathing in soundscapes of the wind. A feeling a daybreak after the storm that begins with silence, encompassing the storm as well as the calm. Like what a baby hears: pure, before the world imposes. 
In the first track, the dialogue tells the perspective of the baby before birth. In the womb, we cannot see, touch, smell, taste—but we can hear. This our first instance of peace, and we unlearn individually and collectively, to get back to that presence.

Radical Empathy - In times of war, listening is rebellion. Somewhere
between ambient, new age, neo soul, vintage erotic soundtracks and
resistance voices, peace sounds human, sensual, and defiant. Voices once
silenced invite us to feel, to love, to build a renewed, inclusive world
where tenderness becomes protest.
Katy Cardie invites you on a journey to Andalusia, where the voices of the gypsies still echo, expressing both the pain of being kept apart and the joy of being together.
Songs that sound like dew even before it rains. My playlist for solace & bedtime :)
A melodramatic clatter of popular music from everywhere infused with hope and love.
